
 1. install piplib :  
     You can download it here : www.piplib.org
 2. Download the Boost header files.
     You can get it here: www.boost.org

 3. Building fada

    $ cd ./fada
    $ ./configure --with-boost=PATH_TO_BOOST

  The script ./configure may not be able to find piplib headers and libraries, in such case you can use '--with-pip-include' and '--with-pip-lib' options :

    $ ./configure --with-pip-include=PATH_TO_PIP_HEADERS --with-pip-lib=PATH_TO_PIP_LIBS
                  --with-boost=PATH_TO_BOOST

  Compiling sources :

    $ make

  and optionally
  
    # make install


 PS:    You may need to update your LD_LIBRARY_PATH

For any other question, please contact us  : 
